details.description: Heist Brewery and Barrel Arts is the second location for Charlotte based Heist Brewery. Featuring a spacious taproom that will be utilized to feature small batch barrel aged offerings, as well as primary brews such as CitraQuench'l and Blurred is the Word. We also are the home of Livy's Neapolitan Pizzeria, open every day that Barrel Arts is. Come enjoy a beer or two, grab a pizza, and relax.

reviews_data.review_text: Great beer. Great vibe
Excellent barrel aged beers.

I was a regular of the NoDa location but have been craving their Kale Cesar, Buffalo Chicken Wrap and of course their Citraquenchel. I decided to try the Barrel Arts location on an afternoon I was nearby. Before going I checked out their online menu to find a very confusing architecture site and nothing on beer or food. So, like a normal person, I called to ask if they were open and if they had the same menu as the NoDa location. The (not so) gentleman who answered the phone thought I was asking if the NoDa location was open to which I clarified my question and explained how I was trying to find their online menu to see if they served food and if it was the same as the NoDa location. He begrudgingly shared that they did serve food and that it was a different menu and remained silent so our conversation ended awkwardly. I was hoping for a bit more guidance or encouragement to come but despite this interaction I headed over to check it out - I was hungry! This was my first time here and I was surprised to see how spacious it was both inside and out. There was no one here at 3pm on a Monday but the bar is incredibly long where the assumed (not so) gentleman was sitting working on his computer and mumbled a half greeting that I couldn’t make out. I approached the bar to check out a menu and finally saw my options, to which I saw a Cesar salad and my beloved Citraquenchel - so was ready to order. I expected someone to come take my order but it was clear he expected me to walk down to him - strange, but okay. I asked if the Cesar salad was the same as the one in NoDa, and he said he didn’t know anything about the NoDa location (and probably realized I was the recent caller). Anyway, I order, he pours my drink and says I can sit anywhere and he’ll bring it out to me. Cool cool cool. 10 min later he brings my salad and plastic cutlery (is this normal for Heist??) and doesn’t say anything. I start to eat when I realize they didn’t give me any croutons, so I call him over and he silently goes to the kitchen and brings back a plate of croutons.  I give him thanks and he doesn’t say anything to me, no apology or check in. Listen, I don’t need much and I get that the service industry is challenging and people have their days - but this entire experience from start to finish was just disappointing. It’s like they don’t want customers or something? Idk - anyway. The salad was just Okay, the biggest silver lining was their CitraQ pour was in a larger glass than NoDa but I won’t be back here seeing as though I wasn’t welcomed in any way. Even as I’m writing a new group came in and I could tell they were confused as to where to go because there is no hostess and the guy just looked at them instead of guiding their experience. Hope this (not so) gentleman realizes service matters. Okay, Rant over - I can’t wait until NoDa location reopens!!

Heist Brewery and Barrel Arts is a fantastic spot with a great variety of beers for craft beer lovers. The Neapolitan wood-fired style pizza is incredible—definitely worth going just for the pizza alone! The location has a cool vibe, offering both indoor and outdoor seating, making it perfect for any occasion. It’s a great place to relax and enjoy some delicious food and drinks with friends. Highly recommend checking it out!

We held our annual end of year celebration at the Heist Brewery Barrell and Arts Room - Skyline Room on Woodard Ave and we have already secured the location for 2025! 10 out of 10 recommend Spencer, Courtney and their team.  The attention to detail was next level!  Having planned and hosted many events in my career, I can honestly say this was the best experience I have ever had with a venue.  They were on site day of the event and were readily available leading up to the event to answer any questions we had and help guide us through the process of planning the event.  The food was delicious, fresh, warm, and we never ran out! They provided a dedicated team of servers just for our event and they were friendly, professional and on top of every need we had.  If you are looking for an event space, I highly recommend checking them out.  You will not be disappointed! The Team at Novant Orthopedics and Sports Medicine - Cotswold
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are so happy that you had such a fantastic time, and appreciate even more that you'll be joining us again in 2025! Cheers, and Happy Holidays from all of us here at Barrel Arts. 🍻

reviews_data.review_text: Hi Heist Brewery! Your beers are wonderful and you're an ace event venue, but did you know that you used to host a real live Phone Booth? I have a map of thousands of locations all over the country for where phone booths used to live, and I'm on a quest to find them. Some are still standing. Some function and still make calls! Most that still exist are only sad empty shells of themselves, disconnected from the lines. In your case, Heist Brewery, I think the saddest thing has happened. Your phone booth was removed completely. Your phone booth has become only a whisper on the wind. A phone booth whisperer, I think I can still hear it. "Is there anything that can be done for me?" it calls out softly. "My purpose in society was always to connect people together easily, privately, anonymously. Can you bring me back?" Heist, I did my best. I've placed a phone booth sticker on your fence. There's a QR code there. If someone scans it, it'll take them to the Great Internet Phone Booth in the Sky, and give that person a free link for another person to join them in a call. But Heist? If you see anybody in shiny leather pants running full out towards the sticker, stop them! We haven't built out that functionality yet.
Never got food. It was very busy.
Went for a wedding. Fun place, great staff! :-)

It looked like they had a Frisbee golf area outside near one of the patio areas.

The music was too loud and overrode the voices of lots of the singers. May be the acoustics. There should be a bigger venue and conducive to music. Seemed well staffed and friendly. Loved the performances. Just be prepared to stand.

The food we got pretzels and beer cheese and pizza bits were very good, especially the beer cheese. Definitely recommend visiting this brewery for beer and food.

reviews_data.review_text: Great food, delicious beer, friendly service, and comfortable seating.

It's so family friendly so you can still be social with little ones running on the grass.  Great beer options and the food is surprisingly good too.
The food menu doesn't change, and there aren't as many options as the other Heist location in NODA.  However outside the lawn is the attraction for us.  Grab a picnic table or bring a blanket, enjoy the music and being outside.

We went on a Monday evening to show a friend from out of town a local brewery and restaurant. We were seated right away on the patio and given a craft of water. We waited 10 to 15 minutes before our server even acknowledged our presence and ordered two beers and a flight.

By this time we had gone through two crafts of water. The server came back to take our order and we still didn't have our drinks and were out of water.  After our server left we had to flag down another server to ask about our drink orders and were told "our bartender is busy."

After 30 minutes our food arrived piecemeal with one entree being dropped off at a time. I asked why our appetizer hadn't arrived and I was told it was on it's way. After another 10 minutes all of our food had been dropped off and we still didn't have our drink orders.  Our appetizer finally arrived after we had begun to eat our entrees.

About five minutes later two of our beers showed up but no flight to which we were given the same excuse of "the bartender is busy."  The flight eventually arrived with our absentee server who asked how everything was going. She left all of our menus on the table to further clutter everything up and then disappeared for another 30 minutes.

raw_data.description: Heist Brewery and Barrel Arts is the second location for Charlotte based Heist Brewery. Featuring a spacious taproom that will be utilized to feature small batch barrel aged offerings, as well as primary brews such as CitraQuench'l and Blurred is the Word. We also are the home of Livy's Neapolitan Pizzeria, open every day that Barrel Arts is. Come enjoy a beer or two, grab a pizza, and relax.

reviews_data.review_text: Great beer. Great vibe
Excellent barrel aged beers.

I was a regular of the NoDa location but have been craving their Kale Cesar, Buffalo Chicken Wrap and of course their Citraquenchel. I decided to try the Barrel Arts location on an afternoon I was nearby. Before going I checked out their online menu to find a very confusing architecture site and nothing on beer or food. So, like a normal person, I called to ask if they were open and if they had the same menu as the NoDa location. The (not so) gentleman who answered the phone thought I was asking if the NoDa location was open to which I clarified my question and explained how I was trying to find their online menu to see if they served food and if it was the same as the NoDa location. He begrudgingly shared that they did serve food and that it was a different menu and remained silent so our conversation ended awkwardly. I was hoping for a bit more guidance or encouragement to come but despite this interaction I headed over to check it out - I was hungry! This was my first time here and I was surprised to see how spacious it was both inside and out. There was no one here at 3pm on a Monday but the bar is incredibly long where the assumed (not so) gentleman was sitting working on his computer and mumbled a half greeting that I couldn’t make out. I approached the bar to check out a menu and finally saw my options, to which I saw a Cesar salad and my beloved Citraquenchel - so was ready to order. I expected someone to come take my order but it was clear he expected me to walk down to him - strange, but okay. I asked if the Cesar salad was the same as the one in NoDa, and he said he didn’t know anything about the NoDa location (and probably realized I was the recent caller). Anyway, I order, he pours my drink and says I can sit anywhere and he’ll bring it out to me. Cool cool cool. 10 min later he brings my salad and plastic cutlery (is this normal for Heist??) and doesn’t say anything. I start to eat when I realize they didn’t give me any croutons, so I call him over and he silently goes to the kitchen and brings back a plate of croutons.  I give him thanks and he doesn’t say anything to me, no apology or check in. Listen, I don’t need much and I get that the service industry is challenging and people have their days - but this entire experience from start to finish was just disappointing. It’s like they don’t want customers or something? Idk - anyway. The salad was just Okay, the biggest silver lining was their CitraQ pour was in a larger glass than NoDa but I won’t be back here seeing as though I wasn’t welcomed in any way. Even as I’m writing a new group came in and I could tell they were confused as to where to go because there is no hostess and the guy just looked at them instead of guiding their experience. Hope this (not so) gentleman realizes service matters. Okay, Rant over - I can’t wait until NoDa location reopens!!

Heist Brewery and Barrel Arts is a fantastic spot with a great variety of beers for craft beer lovers. The Neapolitan wood-fired style pizza is incredible—definitely worth going just for the pizza alone! The location has a cool vibe, offering both indoor and outdoor seating, making it perfect for any occasion. It’s a great place to relax and enjoy some delicious food and drinks with friends. Highly recommend checking it out!

We held our annual end of year celebration at the Heist Brewery Barrell and Arts Room - Skyline Room on Woodard Ave and we have already secured the location for 2025! 10 out of 10 recommend Spencer, Courtney and their team.  The attention to detail was next level!  Having planned and hosted many events in my career, I can honestly say this was the best experience I have ever had with a venue.  They were on site day of the event and were readily available leading up to the event to answer any questions we had and help guide us through the process of planning the event.  The food was delicious, fresh, warm, and we never ran out! They provided a dedicated team of servers just for our event and they were friendly, professional and on top of every need we had.  If you are looking for an event space, I highly recommend checking them out.  You will not be disappointed! The Team at Novant Orthopedics and Sports Medicine - Cotswold
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are so happy that you had such a fantastic time, and appreciate even more that you'll be joining us again in 2025! Cheers, and Happy Holidays from all of us here at Barrel Arts. 🍻

reviews_data.review_text: Hi Heist Brewery! Your beers are wonderful and you're an ace event venue, but did you know that you used to host a real live Phone Booth? I have a map of thousands of locations all over the country for where phone booths used to live, and I'm on a quest to find them. Some are still standing. Some function and still make calls! Most that still exist are only sad empty shells of themselves, disconnected from the lines. In your case, Heist Brewery, I think the saddest thing has happened. Your phone booth was removed completely. Your phone booth has become only a whisper on the wind. A phone booth whisperer, I think I can still hear it. "Is there anything that can be done for me?" it calls out softly. "My purpose in society was always to connect people together easily, privately, anonymously. Can you bring me back?" Heist, I did my best. I've placed a phone booth sticker on your fence. There's a QR code there. If someone scans it, it'll take them to the Great Internet Phone Booth in the Sky, and give that person a free link for another person to join them in a call. But Heist? If you see anybody in shiny leather pants running full out towards the sticker, stop them! We haven't built out that functionality yet.
Never got food. It was very busy.

We went on a Monday evening to show a friend from out of town a local brewery and restaurant. We were seated right away on the patio and given a craft of water. We waited 10 to 15 minutes before our server even acknowledged our presence and ordered two beers and a flight.

By this time we had gone through two crafts of water. The server came back to take our order and we still didn't have our drinks and were out of water.  After our server left we had to flag down another server to ask about our drink orders and were told "our bartender is busy."

After 30 minutes our food arrived piecemeal with one entree being dropped off at a time. I asked why our appetizer hadn't arrived and I was told it was on it's way. After another 10 minutes all of our food had been dropped off and we still didn't have our drink orders.  Our appetizer finally arrived after we had begun to eat our entrees.

About five minutes later two of our beers showed up but no flight to which we were given the same excuse of "the bartender is busy."  The flight eventually arrived with our absentee server who asked how everything was going. She left all of our menus on the table to further clutter everything up and then disappeared for another 30 minutes.

The service at Heist is terrible. We waited for most of our visit with no drinks or food. The only reason I'm giving them two stars and not one is because their food was good.

There are many other bars, restaurants, and breweries in the NoDa area; I suggest you hit any one of them before considering this dump.

Certainly a spacious new addition to the Heist Brewery portfolio with a large special events space too. If you want to beat the crowds of original location try here.
